A worker came to fix the kitchen floor, I pretended to be working from home, but I was actually editing "The Unfinished".
If only this damned file could be opened (OneDrive is total garbage).
* Hacker's voice * I'm in.
He's starting to drill, and the noise is super loud. Great.
I turned the air purifier to the highest setting, it feels a bit too intense, but I did smell the wood shavings, so it's not entirely unreasonable, and to top it off, he's against wearing a mask anyway. Plus, I do need to protect myself, don't I?
I really want to go back to sleep, but he left so I could sleep.
Good news is, Chapter 4 is finally edited!
Chapter 5 is really long, making me super anxious. Yeah! It's so exciting.
Searching and replacing... ➡️ Ellipsis, there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But I still want to emphasize this point. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally excited.
The floor repair worker is sweeping with a vacuum cleaner, hoping that means he'll be done soon.
He went out (sounded like he) was cutting something. I snuck a peek at my progress. Still a lot of work to do :(
There are 7 pages left in Chapter 5. This is still my favorite chapter, and the manuscript is in pretty good shape, mainly some adjustments to formatting, and some minor modifications to active voice and concision. But I really need a break, have a cup of tea, while that guy is still working in my kitchen.
He started using the vacuum cleaner again. Hopefully, this is a good omen.
The floor repair worker in my kitchen is gone!
He told me that the repair price is for the entire floor, but the landlord is too stingy, only willing to pay for the repair of the part near the entrance that has rotted. It feels much better.
I'm drinking tea in the garden, and the air purifier is working hard in the kitchen, purifying the air in the room!
